Since $\angle ROB = 3\angle SOT = 3\angle SOC$, the measure of arc $RB$ is three times the measure of arc $SC$. We also have  \[\angle RTB = \frac{\widehat{RB} - \widehat{SC}}{2}.\] Letting the measure of $\widehat{SC}$ be $x$, we have $\angle RTB = (3x-x)/2 = x$, so $x= 28^\circ$.  Therefore, we have $\widehat{RB} = 3x = 84^\circ$ and $\widehat{SC}=28^\circ$.  Since $\widehat{BC}$ is a semicircle, we have $\widehat{RS} = 180^\circ - \widehat{RB} -\widehat{SC} = 180^\circ - 84^\circ - 28^\circ = \boxed{68^\circ}$.

